The paper deals with the Unbounded Knapsack Problem, which is a well-known problem in the field of algorithms and optimization. The paper presents an improved FPTAS algorithm for the problem, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of algorithms and complexity theory (cs.DS, cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT).
